    <div id="MI" style="top: 131px;">
    	<img src="/images/ScrShoot-CI-small.jpg" alt="Customer Intelligence" />
    	<p style="width: 480px; top: 101px;">As a B2B Software Manufacturer who sources most of our leads through our
 website, we are obviously concerned about how visitors to our site feel
 about it. We used to ask customers to give us their feedback through
 online surveys, but the results were not very useful or dynamic— some
 customers would leave a few comments, but most just would rate and score
 our questions as asked. We really wanted to establish a meaningful
 dialogue with them as individual users of our software. Like many
 businesses, we had also tried a customer forum; however, all the survey
 comments, forum communications and even our sales force notes could not
 help us to parse any actionable insights out of the endless chatter and
 stories. That is, until we found Amplified Analytics and their Customer
 Intelligence Analysis software tool. CI analysis was just the solution we
 needed to help cull clear signals and data out of all the “noise”. Now, we
 encourage customers on our website to tell their stories as elaborately as
 they want and in their own words. We use the Customer Intelligence we
 gather to help us manage our release scopes and schedules based on this
 detailed customer feedback. We are even considering publishing a CI
 analysis summary and an associated next release plan, so that our
 customers can see that their voice is truly driving our decisions.
 Working with Amplified Analytics has really enhanced our dialogue with
 customers and helped us perfect our offerings.</p>
    </div>
    <div id="BEA" style="top: 131px;">
