    	<p style="width: 480px;">Having run 2 high-end restaurants in San Jose successfully, I decided to
 court some new, potential investors with the hopes of opening a third
 restaurant in a new part of the city. The catch was that this time around
 the investors predicated funding on my developing a concise business plan.
 Since I had little experience with market research, I needed to outsource
 the work. Unfortunately, most bids I received were prohibitively expensive
 or entirely generic in their approach. Then one of my investors turned me
 on to online customer opinion mining and I found Amplified Analytics. From
 go, they were right on target— they didn’t need me to come up with
 assumptions about the profile or demographics of my target market.
 Instead, I just gave them the names of 3 or 4 successful restaurants in my
 niche to use as reference. Amplified Analytics was then able to use this
 information to source detailed information on my contemporaries  online
 that I used to create a roadmap for my new venture. It was a seamless and
 elegant solution to my problem— the results were in my hands in a matter
 of days and the cost was 20% below the lowest quote I had received from
 other vendors. We’ve been open now for 5 months and I can safely say that
 I have never experienced such a fast ramp-up after launching a restaurant.
</p>
